definitions.definition: A sport where two opponents attempt to subdue each other in bare-handed grappling using techniques of leverage, holding, and pressure points.
Ellipsis of professional wrestling ( “ act that emulates the sport of wrestling ” ) .
The act of one who wrestles; a struggle to achieve something.
